===Glyph origin===
{{Han etyl}}
{{Han compound|大|t1=person, big|火|t2=fire|ls=ic}} – the color of fire (a person by a fire). The original version is [[𤆍]].

The man on top is simplified as 土 as in [[去]] and [[走]] (< [[𧺆]]). The fire is stylized as well, but an intermediate and obsolete variant is [[灻]].

===Etymology 1===
{{zh-forms|alt=灻,𤆍,烾-ancient,刺-Hokkien}}
Perhaps from {{inh|zh|sit-pro|*qrak||blood; red}}, whence {{cog|bo|ཁྲག||blood}} (STEDT; {{zh-ref|Schuessler, 2007}}). Related to {{och-l|赫|bright red}} and possibly {{och-l|奭|majestic; red}}.

